page.title: 09Day in the life -
page.content: A farmers daughter, Woke up at 7.45 got dressed and had toast for breakfast, then got washed for school I walked to school and arrived about 8.45. at 9.00 I went into school for Assembly. 9.20 read until 9.25 for maths 10.30. Played rounders and did reading. At 12 got washed for dinner then went out to play rounders again. At home I watched the video until my mum returned from School Open Evening. At 16.45 I played tennis against the wall until teatime. At 18.00 we went to cricket match at Crayke. I then went to Nannys and read for a while, then my cousins arrive and I play with them for a bit and then biked to the pub for peanuts, then went home and had supper and went to bed.
